# Glossary

Domain and project-specific terms, so a new contributor (or a future session) doesn't have to reconstruct
meaning from context — and so one term never quietly means two things across the code and docs. Keep
definitions to a line or two; link to the ADR or code where the term is canonically defined.

This is the *engineering* glossary (what `explode walk` means). If the product has user-facing jargon,
that's a separate, user-oriented glossary — don't conflate them.

